This paper deals with the computational complexity of satisfiability problems for fragments of modal dependence logic, which is a logical system used in artificial intelligence and knowledge representation. The paper involves the study of propositional connectives and dependence operators, which are topics that fall under the category of logic and computation (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper deals with complexity classes such as PSPACE and NEXPTIME, which are commonly used in the analysis of algorithms and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also involves the classification of computational complexity for different restrictions of operators, which is a topic that falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the analysis of logical systems and their complexity, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
